@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(DOM-BRIEF, 0027)
' @cycle(DOM-PLAN-SCOPE, 0027)
' @id(DOM-BRIEF)
' @id(DOM-PLAN-SCOPE)
' @desc(DOM-BRIEF, "Implemented as the .mdd/docs/brief.md template (templates::brief / MDD_BRIEF_TEMPLATE), scaffolded SeededOnce by mdd init (write_text_create_if_missing) so a filled-in brief is never clobbered. /mdd-kickoff fills it and the developer signs it off before any model is generated; it is the description /mdd-generate consumes.")
' @desc(DOM-PLAN-SCOPE, "Implemented as extract_scope_ids (parses @scope(<id>,…) from .mdd/ralph/PLAN.md) + Project::plan_scope_ids, plus two mdd validate rules: every PLAN @scope id resolves to an objective @id, and the @scope union covers every implementation-bearing objective @id (USE-/SEQ-/DOM-/CMP-/STM-/MCK-). Both are WARNING and inert unless the PLAN carries @scope. Ralph routes @scope items to a realize-slice cycle, infra items to general tools.")
' Current-side domain for the greenfield kickoff (cycle 0027).
title Greenfield kickoff domain (current)

class Brief {
  + objective : String
  + inScope : List<String>
  + outOfScope : List<String>
  + decisions : List<AdrEntry>
  + tooling : List<String>
  + nfrs : List<String>
  + signedOff : Boolean
}

class AdrEntry {
  + context : String
  + decision : String
  + rationale : String
  + alternatives : String
}

class PlanItem {
  + text : String
  + done : Boolean
  + scope : List<Id>
  + isInfra() : Boolean
}

Brief "1" o-- "*" AdrEntry : records >

note bottom of Brief
  templates::brief() / MDD_BRIEF_TEMPLATE,
  scaffolded create-if-missing by mdd init.
  Signed off before any model is generated
  (OCL-KICKOFF-BRIEF-SIGNED-OFF).
end note

note bottom of PlanItem
  extract_scope_ids + Project::plan_scope_ids
  parse @scope; isInfra() == scope empty. Validate
  warns when a scope id is unknown
  (OCL-KICKOFF-SCOPE-IDS-EXIST) or the union misses
  an impl-bearing objective id
  (OCL-KICKOFF-PLAN-COVERS-OBJECTIVE).
end note
@enduml
